These 4 files allow pgstar to plot a Kippenhan with column depth as the y-axis
For now, the column depth is calculated based on m/mstar coordinates given by default in history
Works as long as the atmosphere is compact (radius constant)
    - star/private/pgstar_kipp.f90           (plotting routines)
    - star/private/pgstar_ctrls_io.f90       (declaring new pgstar options)
    - star/defaults/pgstar.defaults          ("")   
    - star_data/private/pgstar_controls.inc  ("")
    - star/private/mix_info.f90              (printing info about prune_bad_cz_min_Hp_height)

Create the "use_other_close_gaps" option
Thanks to Rob Farmer for the instructions : https://lists.mesastar.org/pipermail/mesa-users/2022-November/014151.html
    - star/defaults/controls.defaults        (default use_other_close_gaps to .false.)
    - star/make/makefile_base                (include other_close_gaps.f90 src file)
    - star/private/ctrls_io.f90              (add use_other_close_gaps in 3 places)
    - star_data/private/star_controls.inc    (add use_other_close_gaps in 1 place)
    - star_data/public/star_data_def.inc     (blank routine other_close_gaps_interface subroutine)
    - star_data/public/star_data.inc         (create pointer for interface procedure) ** this file might be star_data_procedures in newer MESA versions
    - star/other/other_close_gaps.f90        (null definition for other_close_gaps subroutine)
    - star/private/mix_info.f90              (add if close in call_something_gap routines, to call other_close_gaps if required)
